recalls.Summary:
Toyota Motor Engineering & Manufacturing (Toyota) is recalling certain 2014-2016 Toyota 4Runner, 2014-2015 Scion xB, Lexus IS350C, IS250C, 2014 Toyota Sienna, Lexus IS-F, and 2014-2017 Lexus GX460 vehicles sold, or ever registered in the states of Alabama, California, Florida, Georgia, Hawaii, Louisiana, Mississippi, South Carolina, Texas, Puerto Rico, American Samoa, Guam, the Northern Mariana Islands (Saipan), and the U.S. Virgin Islands or "Zone A."   

Toyota is also recalling certain 2011-2013 Toyota Corolla, Corolla Matrix, Lexus IS250, IS350, 2011-2016 4Runner, 2011-2015 Scion xB, Lexus IS350C, IS250C, 2011-2014 Toyota Sienna, Lexus IS-F, 2011-2017 Lexus GX460, and 2011-2012 Lexus ES350 vehicles ever registered in the states of Arizona, Arkansas, Delaware, District of Columbia, Illinois, Indiana, Kansas, Kentucky, Maryland, Missouri, Nebraska, Nevada, New Jersey, New Mexico, North Carolina, Ohio, Oklahoma, Pennsylvania, Tennessee, Virginia, and West Virginia or "Zone B."  

Toyota is also recalling certain 2010-2013 Toyota Corolla, Corolla Matrix, Lexus IS350, 2010-2016 4Runner, 2010-2013 Lexus IS250, 2010-2015 Scion xB, Lexus IS350C, IS250C, 2010-2017 Lexus GX460, 2010-2014 Lexus IS-F, and 2010-2012 Lexus ES350 vehicles ever registered in the states of Alaska, Colorado, Connecticut, Idaho, Iowa, Maine, Massachusetts, Michigan, Minnesota, Montana, New Hampshire, New York, North Dakota, Oregon, Rhode Island, South Dakota, Utah, Vermont, Washington, Wisconsin, and Wyoming or "Zone C."   

These vehicles are equipped with air bag inflators assembled as part of the passenger frontal air bag modules, used as original equipment or replacement equipment (such as after a vehicle crash necessitating replacement of the original air bags), that may explode due to propellant degradation occurring after long-term exposure to high absolute humidity, temperature and temperature cycling.
recalls.Consequence: An inflator explosion may result in sharp metal fragments striking the driver or other occupants resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: Toyota will notify owners.  Depending on the vehicle model, dealers will replace the front passenger air bag inflator, or replace the air bag assembly.  The recall began February 15, 2019.  Owners may contact Toyota customer service at 1-800-331-4331. Toyota's numbers for this recall are "Zone A" Toyota: G0P, Lexus: GLG; "Zone B" Toyota: G0R, Lexus GLH; "Zone C" Toyota: H0A, and Lexus: HLA.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary:
Toyota Motor Engineering & Manufacturing (Toyota) is recalling certain 2010-2016 4Runner, 2003-2006 Tundra, 2003-2013 Corolla, 2009-2010 Corolla Matrix, 2004-2005 RAV4, 2002-2007 Sequoia, 2011-2013 Sienna, 2008-2012 Scion xB, 2008-2009 Lexus IS-F, 2007-2012 Yaris and Lexus ES350, 2010-2017 Lexus GX460, 2002-2010 Lexus SC430, 2006-2012 Lexus IS250 and IS350 and 2010-2015 Lexus IS250C and IS350C vehicles.

These vehicles had their driver or passenger frontal air bag inflators previously replaced under a prior recall using inflators of the same design.  The inflators may explode due to propellant degradation occurring after long-term exposure to high absolute humidity, temperature and temperature cycling.
recalls.Consequence: An inflator explosion may result in sharp metal fragments striking the driver or other occupants resulting in serious injury or death.
recalls.Remedy: Toyota will notify owners.  Depending on the vehicle model, dealers will replace the front driver inflator, front passenger airbag inflator, the airbag assembly, or the front passenger airbag sub-assembly and inflator.  The recall began November 20, 2019.  Owners may contact Toyota customer service at 1-888-270-9371 or Lexus customer service at 1-800-255-3987.  Toyota's numbers for this recall are J0A, J0B, and J0C.  Lexus' numbers for this recall are JLI, JLJ, and JLK.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Southeast Toyota Distributors, LLC (SET) is recalling certain 2011-2016 Toyota Tacoma and 4Runner vehicles equipped with accessory hood scoops installed by SET or SET dealers.  The adhesive attaching the hood scoop may weaken, allowing the hood scoop to detach from the vehicle.
recalls.Consequence: If the hood scoop detaches, it may become a road hazard, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: SET will notify owners, and dealers will mechanically fasten the scoop to the hood, free of charge.  The recall began on September 1, 2017.  Owners may contact SET customer service at 1-954-429-2000.  SET's number for this recall is SET17B.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Southeast Toyota Distributors, LLC (SET) is recalling certain 2015-2018 Toyota 4Runner vehicles equipped with an accessory Billet Grille Overlay installed by SET or provided by SET and installed by SET dealers.  The U-nut that secures the overlay grille may fracture, allowing the Billet Grille Overlay to detach from the vehicle.
recalls.Consequence: If the Billet Grille Overlay detaches while driving, it can become a road hazard, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: SET will notify owners, and dealers will replace the securing U-nuts with upgraded hardware, free of charge.  The recall is expected to begin January 26, 2018.  Owners may contact SET customer service at 1-866-405-4226.  SET's number for this recall is SET17C.
recalls.Notes: Owners may also contact the National Highway Traffic Safety Administration Vehicle Safety Hotline at 1-888-327-4236 (TTY 1-800-424-9153), or go to www.safercar.gov.

recalls.Summary: Gulf States Toyota, Inc. (Gulf States) is recalling certain model year 2015-2016 Toyota 4Runner vehicles manufactured September 22, 2014, to March 23, 2016 and equipped with accessories installed by Gulf States.  The Load Carrying Capacity Modification Label may not reflect the correct added weight of the installed accessories.  As a result, these vehicles fail to comply with the requirements of Federal Motor Vehicle Safety Standard number 110, "Tire Selection and Rims for Passenger Cars."

Toyota Motor Engineering & Manufacturing (Toyota) recalled certain 2018-2019 4Runner, Highlander, Camry, Land Cruiser, Sequoia, Sienna, Tacoma and Tundra, and Lexus RC 300, RC 350, GS 350, GX 460, IS 300, LC 500, LS 500, LX 570, RX 350L, and 2019 Toyota Avalon and Corolla, and certain Lexus NX 300, and ES 350 vehicles on January 13, 2020. 
On March 4, 2020, Toyota expanded the recall to include certain 2014-2015 Toyota 4Runner and Land Cruiser, 2018 Avalon, Corolla, 2014 FJ Cruiser, 2017 Sienna and Lexus 2018 ES 350, 2018-2019 GS 300, 2013-2014 GS350, 2014-2015 GX 460, IS 350 and LX 570, 2014 IS F, 2018-2019 IS 350, LC 500H and LS 500H, 2013-2015 LS 460, 2015 NX 200T and RC350, 2017 RC 200T and RX 350.  Toyota also removed the 2018-2019 Toyota 4Runner and Land Cruiser and 2018-2019 Lexus GX 460 and LX 570 and 2019 NX300 from inclusion in this recall.  On March 19, 2020, Toyota expanded the recall to include 2015 Lexus GS350 vehicles.  The low-pressure fuel pump inside the fuel tank may fail.
recalls.Consequence: If the fuel pump fails, the engine can stall while driving, increasing the risk of a crash.
recalls.Remedy: Toyota will notify owners, and dealers will replace the fuel pump, free of charge.  The recall began May 4, 2020.  Owners may contact Toyota customer service at 1-888-270-9371 or Lexus customer service at 1-800-255-3987.  Toyota's numbers for this recall are 20TB02 and 20TA02 for Toyota vehicles and 20LB01 and 20LA01 for Lexus vehicles.

This is our third Toyota 4Runner with the "X-REAS Sport Enhancement Suspension System".  There has been some type of failure of this system on all 3 of the 4Runners we have owned.  The latest problem with this suspension system on our 2015 4Runner was discovered during a Toyota dealership service appointment at 42,091 miles.  It was recommended the full X-REAS system, front and rear shocks with lines and actuators be completely replaced since both front shocks are leaking fluid at a cost of $4,000.  Since this is our third 4Runner with this suspension and related problems it is our fear that this suspension system might fail when driving and possibly cause an incident with who knows what could happen.  We have brought this to the attention of the Toyota Customer Experience Center and in communication with them they offered to minimally assist financially with repairs, but provided no acknowledgement as to our experience with three 4Runners and this problem plagued suspension system we have encountered.  We declined their assistance since we felt repairing this system and possibly in two or three years being faced with similar repair bills it would be a waste of money on their part as well as ours. In the meantime we continue to drive this vehicle as we need it and we are hopeful that our safety will not be compromised.

issues.title: Premature Lower Ball Joint Failure
issues.description: Lower ball joints fail prematurely, especially on vehicles used for off-roading. The ball joint separates from the control arm, causing dangerous handling issues and potential loss of control.
issues.fix_description: Replace lower ball joints with OEM or upgraded aftermarket units
issues.prevention: Regular inspection during maintenance, avoid extreme off-road conditions

issues.title: Secondary Air Injection System Failure
issues.description: The secondary air injection pump and valves fail, causing check engine lights and emissions issues. Common on higher mileage vehicles.
issues.fix_description: Replace air injection pump, valves, and associated vacuum lines
issues.prevention: Regular maintenance and using quality fuel

issues.title: Rear Window Defogger Failure

issues.fix_description: Rear window replacement or grid line repair kit application
issues.prevention: Avoid scraping ice directly off rear window, use proper cleaning techniques

issues.title: Timing Chain Tensioner Failure

issues.fix_description: Replace timing chain, tensioner, and guides
issues.prevention: Regular oil changes with proper viscosity, avoid extended oil change intervals

issues.title: Transmission Shift Flare
issues.description: 5-speed automatic transmission experiences harsh shifts or flare between gears, particularly 2nd to 3rd gear.
issues.fix_description: Transmission fluid change, software update, or valve body replacement
issues.prevention: Regular transmission fluid changes, avoid aggressive driving

issues.title: Head Unit Display Failure
issues.description: Entune infotainment system display becomes unresponsive, shows black screen, or experiences touch sensitivity issues.
issues.fix_description: Software update or head unit replacement
issues.prevention: Avoid extreme temperatures, regular system updates

issues.title: Exhaust Manifold Crack
issues.description: Exhaust manifold develops cracks, particularly on the passenger side, causing exhaust leaks and potential carbon monoxide exposure.
issues.fix_description: Replace cracked exhaust manifold with updated design
issues.prevention: Allow proper engine warm-up, avoid rapid temperature changes

issues.title: Front Brake Rotor Warping
issues.description: Front brake rotors warp prematurely, especially under heavy use or off-road conditions, causing brake pedal pulsation.
issues.fix_description: Replace or resurface brake rotors, replace brake pads
issues.prevention: Proper break-in procedure, avoid aggressive braking

issues.title: Rear Differential Leak
issues.description: Rear differential develops leaks from the pinion seal or cover gasket, leading to fluid loss and potential damage.
issues.fix_description: Replace pinion seal or cover gasket, refill differential fluid
issues.prevention: Regular inspection and fluid changes, avoid overloading

issues.title: Sunroof Drain Blockage
issues.description: Sunroof drain tubes become blocked with debris, causing water to backup and leak into the cabin interior.
issues.fix_description: Clear drain tubes, replace damaged tubes if necessary
issues.prevention: Regular cleaning of sunroof area, park away from trees

editorial.tagline: Uncompromising off-road capability meets proven reliability
editorial.hero_blurb: The 4Runner TRD Pro stands as Toyota's most hardcore factory off-roader, blending decades of proven truck-based architecture with modern trail-conquering technology. This isn't just an SUV with off-road pretensions—it's a purpose-built adventure machine that prioritizes capability over comfort.
editorial.essence: The TRD Pro represents Toyota's commitment to serious off-road performance without sacrificing the legendary reliability that made the 4Runner name. It's an old-school body-on-frame SUV that refuses to bow to the crossover trend, delivering genuine truck-based durability with factory-backed performance upgrades.
editorial.heritage: Born from Toyota's legendary truck lineage dating back to the 1980s, the 4Runner has remained true to its body-on-frame roots while competitors shifted to car-based platforms. The TRD Pro variant, introduced in 2015, represents the pinnacle of Toyota's off-road engineering expertise developed through decades of desert racing and global expedition experience.
editorial.design_philosophy: Function over form drives every TRD Pro design decision, from the aggressive skid plates to the Fox Racing shocks. Toyota's engineers prioritized ground clearance, approach angles, and component protection while maintaining the rugged aesthetic that signals serious off-road intent.
editorial.motorsport_history: The TRD Pro draws directly from Toyota's Baja racing heritage and decades of off-road competition success. The suspension tuning and underbody protection systems are derived from Toyota's factory race trucks that dominate desert racing events worldwide.
editorial.engine_character: The naturally aspirated 4.0L V6 delivers smooth, predictable power with excellent throttle response at low RPMs—exactly what you want when crawling over rocks or navigating technical terrain. It's not the most powerful engine on paper, but its linear delivery and proven durability make it ideal for serious off-road work.
editorial.transmission_feel: The five-speed automatic prioritizes reliability and smooth operation over quick shifts, with deliberate gear changes that suit the TRD Pro's methodical off-road character. Manual mode provides adequate control for engine braking on steep descents.
editorial.chassis_dynamics: The body-on-frame construction provides exceptional rigidity and durability under stress, while the long-travel Fox shocks soak up serious terrain with remarkable composure. On-road handling is truck-like but predictable, with noticeable body roll but excellent stability.
editorial.steering_feel: Recirculating ball steering offers good feedback for terrain reading while remaining light enough for technical maneuvering. The steering communicates surface changes well without being overly heavy or vague.
editorial.brake_confidence: Four-wheel disc brakes provide strong, fade-resistant stopping power even when loaded down with gear. The pedal feel is firm and progressive, inspiring confidence during steep descents or emergency stops.
editorial.sound_signature: The 4.0L V6 produces a distinctive, purposeful growl under acceleration with a subdued but pleasant exhaust note. Wind noise is noticeable at highway speeds due to the aggressive tire tread and upright stance.
editorial.ideal_owner: Serious off-road enthusiasts who prioritize capability and reliability over luxury features, weekend warriors who need a vehicle that can handle both daily duties and extreme terrain, and anyone who values proven mechanical simplicity over cutting-edge technology.
editorial.not_ideal_for: Buyers seeking fuel efficiency, on-road refinement, or the latest infotainment technology. Those who rarely venture off pavement will find the TRD Pro's compromises hard to justify for daily driving.
editorial.buyers_summary: The TRD Pro commands a significant premium over standard 4Runner models, but delivers genuine factory-backed off-road performance that would cost far more to achieve through aftermarket modifications. Focus on finding examples with complete service records, as the 4.0L V6 thrives with proper maintenance.
